definitions.definition: ( now chiefly attributive ) Clipping of automobile .
examples: My brother is an auto mechanic. He can get me a discount on auto parts.
In 1909, his grandfather was the first farmer in the county to buy an auto .

definitions.definition: ( uncountable ) A setting for automatic operation.

examples: A body-coloured centre pillar signalled the arrival of an electronic four-speed auto , slight suspension revisions and minor trim changes.

definitions.definition: ( automotive ) A car with an automatic gearbox/transmission.
examples: It wasn't too bad but we did hire an auto (couldn't imagine changing gears with my right hand).

main_definition: ( now chiefly attributive ) Clipping of automobile .
secondary_definitions: ( uncountable ) A setting for automatic operation.
( automotive ) A car with an automatic gearbox/transmission.

examples: Users are often unable to note down the number of the taxi or the auto as the driver will just zoom past.
